description: Fasten your seat belts and get ready for the carnival of cartoon talent that is BLAB! America's premier anthology of cutting-edge comics and illustration art is back with its most spectacular volume yet. Sporting all-new front and back covers by acclaimed painter Mark Ryden, whose work has graced the covers of everything from Juxtapoz magazine to Screaming Trees albums, this volume should be the sharpest-looking object on any bookshelf. Vol. 11 features ten more pages of color than previous volumes, and welcomes ten new artists to the BLAB! family. It also features the return of BLAB!'s most popular favorites, including comics giants Richard (The Chuckling Whatsit) Sala, Peter (The New York Times) Kuper, Lloyd (Troubletown) Dangle, Drew (Private Lives of Public Figures) Friedman, Spain (Zap) Rodriguez, and Doug (Steven) Allen, as well as illustration legends David Goldin, Christian Northeast, Gary Baseman, Jonathon Rosen, and more. BLAB! is edited and designed by Monte Beauchamp. Under his guidance,BLAB! is more than an anthology ‚Äî it's an objet d'art worthy of a coffee-table near you.

description: In the Bolivian salt deserts there is a legend about the T√¨o, the devil who lives underground. Now the T√¨o seems to have awoken and he appears to have two elusive and very skilled undead gunmen. Faceing them, Harlan, Tesla and Kurjak will have the greatest surprise of their lives. Their opponents are two reluctant vampires, two Wild West old-timers, hardened rebels who have no intention of being the servants of a Master of the Night. That‚Äôs probably their fate, though, and Kurjak could be forced to kill two of his legendary childhood heroes...

description: An old cajun melody from the Thirties, a folk valzer with dark rhythms... In the maze of canals people kept vanishing for decades and the only trace they left is that old song... When three musicology students, friends of Professor Milius‚Äôs, disappear, Harlan and Kurjak go to the Louisiana bayou, determined to find out who is the mythological creature called Saman Patou...

description: In South Los Angeles, the bloodthirsty Mara Salvatrucha gang has a new invincible leader. The ‚Äúvigilante‚Äù serial killer, Jeff Carter, determined to wipe out the criminal organization, realizes that he cannot do it alone, this time. While the LAPD Homicide Department gets on Jeff‚Äôs tracks, with English detective Ann Spade as a consultant, Harlan, Kurjak, Tesla and a couple of old friends of theirs arrive to the city. Their goal is Bugsy, brought back to life, the mobster turned vampire!

description: ‚ÄúOrpheus, in front of the Elf King, grabbed his harp and began to sing‚Äù... For years, Duncan McGillivray hid the existence of the mysterious ‚ÄúBallad of King Orpheus‚Äù that he heeded in the wind of the Scottish moorlands. Now the song that takes people to death and ill fate has been rearranged by the folk band of his disciple Stuart Morison. Old Duncan wants to prevent the song to be played at Byrnestane Castle, the in the Dark Ages was the seat of the unnameable and bloody rites of the evil Lord Soules and his servant Redcap. But the ghost hunterers from York University are in Byrnestane, too, for a congress about Celtic culture. According to the medium Maud Nightingale, though, there aren‚Äôt any ghosts in that place! At least, until the melody of the ballad echoes inside the ancient walls... then, with the help of young Stuart, our vampire and ghost hunterers will have to face the specters at the orders of the terrible Lord Soules...
name: La ballata di Re Orpheus

description: Two of the most famous mummified corpses of the Capuchin Crypt are walking around! In the streets of Palermo, a strange series of murders begins... The Mafia can‚Äôt allow being accused of these crimes, and Don Tano‚Äôs henchmen begin to hunt the two living corpses. Also Harlan and Kurjak are looking for them, because, behind their strange resurrection, there‚Äôs a mysterious Black Rock, endowed with magical powers...
name: Rosalinda delle zagare

description: During the 1970s, the colored people were evacuated from District Six, in Cape Town. The old Becky is the keeper of the neighborhood‚Äôs memories: she sees the ghosts of the former dwellers and talks to them. She also knows that behind the property speculation and the recent deaths there isn‚Äôt a gang war, but the hand of a Master of the Night and his ruthless vampires...
name: I fantasmi di Distretto 6

description: Carnival has ended, but two mysterious masks still roam the canals and the deserted streets of Venice. And people vanish into thin air. After a strange fire in Palazzo Navager, Father Alvise suspects that the disappearances are connected with the legendary living doll that the magic artificer Jerome Sombre invented during the 1700, a creature that was also loved by Giacomo Casanova...
name: La bambola veneziana

description: The Devil, the Magician, the Hanged Man... When Edgardo Zani read the tarot pack of the Visconti of Milan, he got these three figures. the fourth he was sent in an anonymous envelope: the Tower... Just like the one surviving tower of Palace Gorani-Crivelli, in Milan, where at nighttime somebody saw a strange ghost climber. But the Tower emblem is also connected to the mysterious lost crown ‚Äì that belonged to the Emperor Constantine and held the relics of the Holy Cross ‚Äì now partially preserved in Monza. Where are the missing parts of the crown? During which age had they been stolen? Who plays the part of the Magician? And who‚Äôs the Devil? Who‚Äôs the mysterious ‚ÄúHanged Man‚Äù, entangled in the swirl of the Eternal Return? For Harlan and Kurjak, guests of the well-read primary school teacher Zani in the Lombard capital, it‚Äôs the beginning of the diffcult solution of the most intricate puzzle of their career.
name: La corona di ferro

description: Is the Count of Saint-Germain still in play? Or did he hand things over to his loyal friend Gorani? Are the bandits of the Merlata still the defenders of the crown? Who is the mysterious Inquisitor and who‚Äôs he working for? What‚Äôs the secret of the ‚Äútime box‚Äù that holds the violin and the diary of Luciano Barelli? The clues gathered in various times will lead to a magical place near Milan, Italy, where the final clash between demons and vampires will take place, with Harlan, Kurjak and Tesla as special guests.

You call in a xenotech, a specialist in intuiting alien motivations and solving problems. Someone who can get the job done. Someone like Keif Llama. Reprints stories from the Fantagraphics series as a prelude to the new Keif Llama series also starting this month.

When Judge Dredd comes face-to-face with one of his clones he knows that the rookie may well be his replacement one day. Old Stoney Face isn't getting any younger and as he shows the new recruit around the streets of Mega-City One he reminisces about his dead clone brother Rico. Out of respect for Dredd, the clone decides to take on Rico's name but will he also share Rico's fate?

description:
The X-Men's base on Utopia Island comes under attack from old enemies: Lady Deathstrike and the Reavers! Wolverine leads X-Force against them, but will his new team be exposed to Cyclops?!

By Rick Remender and Rafael Albuqurtque

Also: Deadpool sees double when he encounters a pair of identical Steve Rogers, thanks to the maniacal Doctor Bong!

By Daniel Way and Carlo Barber

Includes material reprinted from Uncanny X-Force #5.1 and 5, and Deadpool #29.

The Deathlok invasion has begun! Wolverine, Deadpool, Fantomex, Psylocke and Archangel enter The World ‚Äì the super-science environment where a new horror awaits!

Also: Deadpool tackles an infestation of vampires in a solo tale!

Includes material reprinted from Uncanny X-Force #6-7 and Deadpool #30.

HALF HUMAN... ALL KILLER!

Sergeant Nate Slaughterhouse is the veteran of many bloody wars fought on alien planets, but after being mortally wounded on the battlefield the only way to save his life is to cybernetically reconstruct his body, turning him into more machine than man ‚Äì a mandroid!

Discharged from the army Nate returns to Mega-City One, struggling to deal with his new existence. When his family are subject to a vicious attack his bitterness turns to anger, and he takes to the streets to dispense brutal vigilante justice. But there‚Äôs room for only one law in the Big Meg‚Ä¶ And Dredd‚Äôs on the case!

Written by John Wagner (A History of Violence) with art by Kev Walker (ABC Warriors), Simon Coleby (Low Life) and Carl Critchlow (Lobster Random) this dark tale of revenge is 2000 AD at its pulse-pounding best!

THIS VOLUME INCLUDES THE STORIES

Legsy Diamond: Model by day... care-free adventurer by night. She's part of a team of hot fun-loving babes who shoot guns, ride motorcycles, and kick butt...and maybe fight some crime along the way. Jump into their first exciting adventure as the stunning gals must recover a priceless gem... the legendary Heart of Josephine diamond, which was stolen by (you guessed it) evil, sexy babes! Packed with action, mystery, intrigue and humor. Fans of the fast-paced Alias TV show will love this rip-roarin' adventure.

DREDD GUNS FOR JUSTICE!

Welcome to Sector House 301, the isolated dumping ground for Mega-City One‚Äôs every misfit and foul-up Judge. Nicknamed The Pit, the sector house holds many dark secrets, and the discovery of one of them may have lead to the death of Sector Chief Rohan.

Sent to take over The Pit is Judge Dredd. Together with a small team of trusted Judges, he uncovers a trail of de-ceit and murder that leads to the very top levels of command. The only question is, will Dredd live long enough to bring the culprits to Justice?

Written by Dredd co-creator John Wagner (A History of Violence) and including art by comic legend Carlos Ezquerra (The Boys), this is Judge Dredd at its very best!

The newest Collector's Edition is here at last!!! The Hulk leads a new team: Skaar, She-Hulk, A-Bomb, Korg, the Red She-Hulk and Lyra! When Earth faces destruction from the rogue planet K'ai, the Hulks become the world's only hope! Who is the dreaded Hiro-Kala, and how will he change the Hulk's life forever?

Don‚Äôt miss the start of a new era of adventure!

Plus: special fact-files revealing the history of the Hulk and his new team!

Includes material reprinted from Incredible Hulks #612-614.

The Hulk confronts his mad son Hiro-Kala! To save Earth from destruction, will the Hulk kill his own flesh and blood ‚Äì or will he leave the job to Bruce Banner?!

By Greg Pak, Ben McCool,Tim Seeley,Tom Raney, Scott Hanna and Barry Kitson.

Also: The Red Hulk begins a series of solo adventures! Iron Man attacks in ‚ÄòScorched Earth‚Äô!

By Jeff Parker and Gabriel Hardman.

Includes material reprinted from Incredible Hulks #615-616 and Hulk #25.

Big changes are happening for Spider-Man: Bigger threats, bigger guest-stars, and a big opportunity that could turn Peter Parker's life around! Guest starring The Avengers and The Fantastic Four!

Also, classic adventure, as The Acts of Vengeance continue! Spider-Man battles Shocker, Hydro-Man and The Rhino, but even with his cosmic powers will it be enough to defeat Doctor Doom?!!

Includes material reprinted from Amazing Spider-Man #648 and Peter Parker: The Spectacular Spider-Man #160!

"WOODSTOCK" PROPELS PEANUTS INTO THE '70s!

He turns up first as Snoopy‚Äôs secretary, then gradually becomes a good friend whom Snoopy helps to fly South... but it‚Äôs not until June 22, 1970 that the little bird gains a name, in a perfect salute to the decade that ends with this volume: Woodstock!

In other timely stories, Peppermint Patty runs afoul of her school‚Äôs dress code (those sandals!), Lucy declares herself a ‚ÄúNew Feminist,‚Äù and Snoopy‚Äôs return to the Daisy Hill Puppy Farm on a speaking engagement climaxes in a riot and a new love found amidst the teargas (‚ÄúShe had the softest paws...‚Äù).

Speaking of Snoopy, this volume falls under the sign of the Great Beagle, as three separate storylines focus on the mysterious sovereign of Beagledom. First Snoopy is summoned by a wrathful G.B. when Frieda submits a complaint about his (Snoopy‚Äôs) desultory rabbit-chasing efforts; then, back in the Great one‚Äôs good graces, Snoopy is sent on a secret mission; and finally he himself ascends (briefly!) to the mantle of Great Beagledom.

In other news, an exasperated Lucy throws Schroeder‚Äôs piano into the maw of the kite-eating tree, with gruesome results... Miss Othmar goes on strike and Linus gets involved... Charlie Brown‚Äôs baseball team has an actual (brief) winning streak... Snoopy‚Äôs quest to compete in the Oakland ice skating competition is thwarted by his inability to find a partner... Charlie Brown goes to a banquet to meet his hapless baseball hero Joe Shlabotnik... Snoopy is left in the Van Pelt family‚Äôs care as Charlie and Sally Brown head out of town for a vacation... and (alas) the Little Red-Haired Girl moves away...

This volume also features a new introduction by renowned illustrator Mo Willems and, as always, gorgeous design by award-winning cartoonist Seth.

description: The Sire returns! Donald Wright was just a lowly secretary before being transformed into the Sire - a superhuman forced to fight evil by his own costume! Now, following the events of the first mini-series, he's come to accept the power he wields, but will he accept his mission? You'll never guess who it puts him at odds with if he does.

Still in the deluxe 10" by 10" format, this volume may be the best yet. It features work by usual suspects Blanquet, Walter Minus, Peter Kuper (a full-color Winsor McKay tribute strip), Peter Hoey, Spain, Doug Allen and Matti Hagleberg, as well as newcomer Greg Clarke, two superb full-page illustrations by Drew Friedman, lots of Baseman, the four-page full-color "Toilet Train" by none other than DEVO's Mark Mothersbaugh, a crazy vintage nudie-photo continuity from France (ooh la la!), more Krampus cards, some typically wild BLAB! text pieces, plus covers and a painted four-page story by the Clayton Brothers!
